Colin L. Powell







Download Vcard


Colin L. Powell
Associate
After graduating from Baylor University School of Law, Colin began his legal career at HDBD with a focus in product liability.
Before joining the firm, Colin worked as an intern at the U.S. Attorney’s Office in Dallas, Texas, where he conducted research and was responsible for drafting on criminal practice and procedure issues. Prior to graduation, Colin served as a summer associate at the firm and gained experience working on personal injury cases.
In 2011, Colin graduated magna cum laude with a Bachelor of Arts degree in History from Baylor University. While attending law school, he won numerous awards for his impressive efforts in mock trial competitions, and was the winner of the 2013 Bob and Karen Wortham “Top Gun” Fall Practice Court Mock Trial Competition.
Telephone: 214.346.3790
            Fax: 214.267.4280
            cpowell@hdbdlaw.com
          	8750 N. Central Expy.
            Suite 1600
          	Dallas, Texas  75231
          






Curriculum Vitae


Education

			      Baylor University, J.D. 2014 • National Trial Competition Mock Trial Team • Tournament of Champions Mock Trial Team • American Association of Justice Mock Trial Team (Regional Semifinalist) • National Criminal Procedure Moot Court Team (Third-Place Brief) • Dawson & Sodd Spring Moot Court Competition SemifinalistBaylor University, B.A. History (magna cum laude) 2011
			    




Bar & Court Admissions

			      TexasU.S. District Court for the Northern District of Texas
			    




Honors & Awards

			      • Winner of the 2013 Bob and Karen Wortham "Top Gun" Fall Practice Court Mock Trial Competition• Scott, Douglass & McConnico, L.L.P. Evidence Award from Baylor Law American Board of Trial Advocates Award from Baylor Law School
			    




Professional Affiliations & Activities

			      • Waco I.S.D. Education Foundation Board Member, 2011-2014• Heart of Texas Regional History Fair Judge, 2009-2012
			    




Areas of Practice



  
  
  
  	Personal Injury Defense
  

  



  
  
  
  	Product Liability Litigation
  

  









 
 
 
 






















 



